## VI, 42. Charm to appease anger.

1\. As the bowstring from the bow, thus do I take off thy anger from thy
heart, so that, having become of the same mind, we shall associate like
friends!  
2. Like friends we shall associate-I take off thy anger. Under a stone
that is heavy do we cast thy anger.  
3. I step upon thy anger with my heel and my fore-foot, so that, bereft
of will, thou shalt not speak, shalt come up to my wish!

